    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-05-19T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-05-19T10:00:00-05:00" n="472"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/5–1950: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McDonald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-05-19T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 19, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>380. Shiloah with Kollek at residence May 19 told me message was received from
                    Amman May 16 inquiring re Shiloah return. Latter expects date for meeting with
                    King to be fixed within few days. Shiloah emphatic King must personally
                    participate during early stages negotiations if these are to succeed; later they
                    might be transferred to <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> offices Geneva.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 380, repeated Jerusalem 35, Department pass Amman 38, Moscow 28,
                    Geneva 30, London 84.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McDonald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
